<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Offers To Prolong Special Tariff Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3001014094 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 25 
Jan 94 p 18 </F>

<F P=103> PA3001014094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] French President Francois Mitterrand and Foreign 
Minister Alain Juppe have offered Colombian Foreign Minister 
Noemi Sanin de Rubio their full support in getting the European 
Union (EU) to prolong the special tariff privileges program for 
Colombian products. 
  After a meeting scheduled to last 15 minutes, but which 
lasted an hour, the Colombian diplomat said Colombia will be 
able to sell almost all its products to the 12 EU countries 
without paying duties. She added that such conditions would be 
applicable for a period of four or 10 years, depending on 
Colombia's request, to begin when the current agreement expires. 
  Noemi Sanin visited France in December and met with French 
officials to expound on the country's achievements, the 
government modernization policy, the strengthening of the 
judicial system, the efforts to counter drug trafficking, the 
peace process with the guerrillas, and the defense of human 
rights. 
  The possibility of France investing in our products, 
including bananas, and the repercussions for Colombia -- 
especially the Uraba region -- would be a positive step that 
would further expand Colombia's participation in the foreign 
market. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

