<H3> <TI>   Army Protests U.S. Decision To Cancel Passports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2801221594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2801221594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The General Command of the Haitian Armed Forces 
[FADH] denounces the motive behind the 26 January statements by 
by the U.S. Embassy spokesman in Haiti, which announce the 
cancellation, over the next few days, of officers' visas. This 
calculated measure is shameful blackmail aimed at destabilizing 
another national Haitian institution and taking it hostage, the 
General Headquarters press release adds. 
  The communique issued by FADH General Headquarters stresses 
that the ideal of the Haitian military, nourished by the lessons 
of its national history, is concerned with duty to country, thus 
enablling the unified military institution to continue defending 
the ideals of freedom, sovereignty, and greatness, which have 
always roused the Haitian people. 

</TEXT>

