<H3> <TI>   Labor Unions Protest Employers' Work Stoppage </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2801215994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2801215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The labor unions, CATH [Autonomous Organization of 
Haitian Workers], CGT [General Central of Workers], CTH 
[Confederation of Haitian Workers], FOS [Federation of Workers 
Trade Unions], OGITH [General and Independent Organization of 
Haitian Workers], and KOTA [Confederation of Haitian Blue-Collar 
Workers] protest the employers' initiative to stop work. The 
labor union sectors see those arrangements as unilateral and the 
coup de grace to the workers' organizations, which will become 
organizations of unemployed people. 
  According to members of the labor unions, the employers' 
associations want only to avoid their responsibilities in paying 
the workers. The various labor unions are ready to meet with the 
other sectors of national life to search for a solution to the 
Haitian crisis. 

</TEXT>

