Being Built </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2801154494 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 25 
Jan 94 p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PA2801154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Colombian Navy has announced that the U.S. 
Marines will return to their bases at the beginning of March. 
The Marines are building a river base in Puerto Lopez, Meta. 
The Colombian Navy also denied that the U.S. Marines are 
building an airport in Juanchaco, Valle. 
  Admiral Hernando Garcia Ramirez, commander of the Colombian 
Navy, has asserted that the U.S. troops will return to their 
bases in the United States once they finish building the school 
and the health center. He also denied charges that the U.S. 
Marines, stationed in Malaga Bay, are building an airport in 
Juanchaco. 

