<H3> <TI>   Police Spokesperson Says 1 Bomb Defused, Another Explodes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3101125294 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 1219 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA3101125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jorge Celis] </F>
  [Text] The National Police public relations spokesperson 
reports on last night's bomb scares. One of the bombs was 
defused, and the other exploded at 12th Street and 19th Avenue 
in Zone One. 
  [Begin unidentified spokesperson recording] Two bomb scares 
were being handled. One was defused at 40th Street and 3d 
Avenue in Zone Three, behind the quarters of the National Police 
1st Brigade [words indistinct]. The other, a fragmentation 
grenade, was thrown against a house. We cannot assume the last 
one was part of the terrorist actions that have been taking 
place in Guatemala City. We believe it could have been hurled at 
a private home, but we do not know which one, perhaps by someone 
who was inebriated. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

