<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Reports Rebel Attacks in Ocosingo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3101201094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1730 GMT 31 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA3101201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 31 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- The Defense 
Secretariat has reported new attacks on civilians in Ocosingo 
Municipality, Chiapas State, although the Army is observing a 
cease-fire. Defense Secretariat Communique No. 27 stated that 
armed groups attacked Indian villages that refused to cooperate 
with the self-styled Zapatist National Liberation Army. The 
communique added that 56 families were evicted with excessive 
violence from Santa Elena, La Soleda, San Francisco, and San 
Miguel Villages. The families were later given shelter by the 
Rural Association of Common Interest [Asociacion Rural de 
Interes Colectivo] in Ocosingo Municipality in eastern Chiapas. 
  The 7th Military Region Command received 27 complaints from 
cattle ranchers in Ocosingo and Altamirano of looting by 
aggressor groups. The office reported that on 27 January the 
person in charge of one of the ranches attacked in Ocosingo had 
stated that a group of 50 armed persons destroyed the ranch he 
was guarding. 
  Near the Miguel Hidalgo ranches in Ocosingo, some 500 armed 
individuals have surrounded 1,460 residents of nearby villages, 
asking them for food and a "war tax" and threatening to kill 
them if they do not join the armed movement. 
  A report received on 29 January stated that armed groups 
burned four wooden houses and used mallets to destroy three 
brick houses located close by the San Cristobal de las 
Casas-Ocosingo highway near Nuevo Oxchuc village, the communique 
added. 
  Residents of the 10 April and San Bartolo Ejidos went to 
military installations in Comitan on Sunday to ask for help in 
evacuating the refugees and to ask for food since armed groups 
are blocking the roads. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-32061 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat021_k_94001" </HT>


