<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Camacho: Conditions for Talks With Rebels Exist </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0102150994 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0102150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Manuel Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in Chiapas, met today with President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari in Los Pinos. Afterward, he met with senators 
and deputies from the Plural Group [grupo plural) in his office 
to follow-up on events in Chiapas. The congressional Standing 
Committee created this group, and it comprises 10 legislators 
representing the six registered political parties. They talked 
about the need to find a negotiated and peaceful solution to the 
Chiapas conflict above any partisan stand. 
  Camacho said the conditions for dialogue exist, and he 
highlighted three points that will be discussed with the armed 
groups. These points are: 
  1. Economic demands relating to the material conditions of 
the Chiapas Indians. 
  2. Social demands relating to racism, neglect, poverty, 
disrespect, expulsions, and attacks on culture and traditions. 
  3. Political demands relating to the Chiapas Indians' lack 
of 
legal room for true participation. Camacho will make a public 
announcement tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

