<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Camacho Acknowledges EZLN Communique </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0202034694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0258 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0202034694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] San Cristobal de Las Casas, 1 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- 
Manuel Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace in Chiapas, today 
described as "an important step" toward peace a recent 
communique issued by the armed group [Zapatist National 
Liberation Army, EZLN] operating in Chiapas. The EZLN 
communique states that a direct dialogue is "imminent." 
  The message is "an important step toward meeting and 
advancing the process for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas 
State," Camacho Solis said in a communique released to the media 
in San Cristobal, 1,200 km southeast of Mexico City. [passage 
omitted] 
  Camacho Solis, in his second communique issued on 1 
February, 
termed as an additional advancement the fact that the group is 
willing to broaden media coverage of the possible direct 
dialogue. 
  The armed group also agreed today to Camacho Solis' proposal 
for national and foreign journalists to cover the eventual 
negotiations, but the group excluded the private Mexican 
television networks Televisa and Television Azteca. 
  Camacho Solis responded: "My stance is not to exclude anyone 
and to make accreditation and access to the talks subject only 
to the appropriate security measures." 
  The commissioner deemed "appropriate the EZLN's suggestion 
for the registration of the media and the procedures for 
coverage to be carried out through the group's mediator, Bishop 
Samuel Ruiz Garcia." 
  Camacho Solis, in his first communique today read this 
morning in San Cristobal de Las Casas, proposed to the armed 
group the creation of two "buffer zones" without an armed 
presence to ease the situation and help the civilian population. 
  Camacho Solis also announced that the Mexican Army has 
withdrawn from the towns in the conflict area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

