<F P=106> [From the "Guatemala Flash" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Rodolfo Rosales Garcia Salas, Revolutionary Civic 
Alliance leader, termed yesterday's referendum results a 
political earthquake. The yes vote won over the no vote by a 
minimal margin, which means that the Ramiro de Leon Carpio 
government, and especially the politicians, received one of 
their worst setbacks because most of the population did not vote. 
  The controversial politician said the president should 
abstain from making decisions to solve the country's crisis 
because it is obvious that the Guatemalan people have rejected 
the package of constitutional reforms that Congress approved. 
These constitutional reforms were also backed by presidential 
scheming, which translates as a deep rejection of the 
traditional political classes and the maneuvers of President 
Ramiro de Leon Carpio. 

</TEXT>

