<H3> <TI>   CONACOM Favors Conference Following Aristide Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0102231894 Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM in French 1500 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0102231894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A national conference held without the participation 
of all sectors risks being just one more conference, according 
to the National Congress of Democratic Movements, CONACOM. 
  In a press release published 31 January, CONACOM called for 
the holding of a true national conference and proposed a 
schedule, including five steps, for the holding of this 
conference. 
  CONACOM says that such a conference must be preceded by: 
  A. The formation of a political coalition among the 
political 
  groups that agree to work jointly for a way out of the 
  crisis; 
  B. The designation by President Aristide of a new prime 
minister; 
  C. The formation of a government of national concord; 
  D. The holding of a sociopolitical rally; and 
  E. The holding of a national conference following Aristide's 
return to Haiti. 
  CONACOM rejects an arrangement precipitated in form and time 
[as heard] and invites all the country's sons to be aware of the 
seriousness of the crisis. 

</TEXT>

