<H3> <TI>   DeRonceray Warns Against National Conference `Industry' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0202002994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0202002994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The various national conference projects are not 
well regarded by some political parties. Hubert De Ronceray is 
still in favor of the application of Article 149 of the 
Constitution to solve the political crisis. The leader of MDN 
[Mobilization for National Development] warns against what he 
calls the newborn national conference industry. Professor De 
Ronceray who reviewed news highlights for the month of January, 
stopped on three facts: 
  First, the congress at the national theater. Second, the 
decision of Haitian employers to shut down commerce and industry 
from 28 January to 9 February. Third, the new industry of 
national conferences. 
  Hubert De Ronceray expressed his concern that certain 
initiatives have the effect of surgery that immediately kills 
the patient instead of saving him. While condemning the embargo 
which, according to MDN, has wrecked the economic and social 
institutions and is forcing 5 million people to despair or 
revolt, Hubert De Ronceray has urged the country's powerful 
forces to remain vigilant around Article 149 of the 1987 
Constitution and avoid the false path born of confusion and 
despair. 

</TEXT>

