<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paraguayan President Wasmosy Signs Joint Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0102165894 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0102165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Newspaper of the Airwaves" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Paraguayan President Juan Carlos Wasmosy and 
Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori have signed a joint 
political, economic, and cultural declaration at the Government 
Palace. The document was signed during the first official trip 
by Wasmosy, who was democratically elected. 
  Wasmosy arrived at the Peruvian Air Force's 8th Group in 
Lima 
at 1050. He was accompanied by the foreign affairs and industry 
ministers. At the 8th Group, he was welcomed with a 21-gun 
salute and met by Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori, ministers 
of state and congressmen, following which the National Police 
band played the Peruvian and Paraguayan national anthems. 
  After the welcoming ceremony, President Wasmosy and Peruvian 
Foreign Minister Efrain Goldenberg went to the Heroes of 
Independence Park to place wreaths on monuments to the nation's 
heroes. At the park, Wasmosy extended a message of brotherhood 
to the Peruvian people and reiterated his pledge to strengthen 
Paraguay's ties of friendship with Peru. 
  Wasmosy will lunch with Fujimori at 1330 in the formal 
dining 
room at the Government Palace. He will visit the Democratic 
Constituent Congress at 1600 and then he will attend a solemn 
session of Lima's Municipal Council, during which he will be 
declared an illustrious visitor and will be given the keys to 
the city. 

</TEXT>

