<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bishops Chairman Endorses Tax Increase in Economic Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0102223794 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0102223794 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bishop Luciano Mendes de Almeida, chairman of the 
National Conference of Brazilian Bishops [CNBB], defends the tax 
increase foreseen in the government economic plan. Bishop Mendes 
said this measure is necessary to guarantee resources for 
national social programs. The CNBB chairman considers Congress' 
decision not to increase the taxes paid by large companies an 
injustice. 

</TEXT>

