<H3> <TI>   Health Care Agreement Signed With Misiones, Argentina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0202172594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0202172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 1 February, Cuba and the Argentine province of 
Misiones reached agreement on a compensated exchange of products 
and established formulas for putting this mutually beneficial 
collaboration into practice. Misiones Province Governor Federico 
Ramon Puerta and Acting Foreign Trade Minister German Amado 
Blanco signed the document, which will strengthen economic ties 
between the two nations. 
  The agreement proposes that Misiones Province send our 
island 
mainly lumber and paper, while Cuba would supply certain 
medicines, medical advice [asesoria], and specialized health 
services. Morever, according to what was learned at the signing 
of the cooperation agreement in Havana, a group of Cuban 
physicians will provide technical assistance in developing a 
primary health care program in Misiones Province. The agreement 
calls for a team of four experts in general medicine, a nurse, 
and a dentist to go to Misiones within the next few months to 
act as consultants in applying their Family Doctor Program 
experience to local conditions in Misiones. 

</TEXT>

