<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Protests Over World Bank Director's Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0202223694 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0202223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brazilian Ambassador to the United States Paulo 
Tarso Flecha de Lima has sent a protest letter to the president 
of the World Bank over the statement by World Bank Director Said 
Hussein. 
  During a speech to the America's Society, which groups most 
of the bankers with whom Brazil is renegotiating its foreign 
debt, Hussein said Brazil is the biggest cloud on the Latin 
American horizon. 
  In his letter, the Brazilian ambassador said he is surprised 
at this statement because a World Bank official like Hussein 
cannot denigrate the image of a country which that bank should 
help. 

