<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leftists Make Declaration for Action, Unity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0202203694 Lima LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 19 Jan 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> PY0202203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima LA REPUBLICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 
<H6>  Declaration for a Democratic and Sovereign Peru With Peace 
Based on Social Justice </H6>
  Those of us who sign this declaration have begun talks 
seeking to generate a current of action and thought that will 
permit us to converge for the creation of a broadly based 
Promotion Committee in order to unite the left and people's 
movement. This committee will be integrated with representatives 
of political parties and movements; regional leaders; labor, 
neighborhood, and youth leaders; and progressive leaders. They 
will combine the efforts of Peruvian social and political 
movements to propose political initiatives and actions for a 
democratic alternative to the country. They also will represent 
citizens' aspirations for peace with social justice in order to 
fight the neoliberal project and Alberto Fujimori's 
authoritarian government's attempt to stay in power. 
  This is a starting point for a dialogue and a new attitude 
for the democratic and socialist left. From this platform we 
want to promote the broadest programmatic debate possible in 
light of the latest changes in Peru and the world and in order 
to generate a new practice with people's and social forces. It 
also is the beginning of an intense collective reflection on our 
role in Peruvian national life in the past decades, a reflection 
with deep self-criticism on past mistakes and the commitment to 
overcome them in order to assume the responsibilities the people 
and Peru demand of us. 
  We wish to call on all those who individually or 
collectively 
-- and from a socialist, democratic, and deeply Peruvian 
perspective -- might want to join our efforts and commit 
themselves to fight for a modern and efficient economy 
implemented with solidarity; for the full implementation of 
social and political rights; for the country's moralization; and 
for respect for human rights. Those who join us will be involved 
in the construction of a National Project for Development, 
Modernization, Decentralization, with Sovereignty and Peace, and 
Based on Social Justice in order to make our country really 
viable. 
  To this effect, we will promote numerous regional and local 
events nationwide to discuss in an ample and democratic manner 
your opinions regarding the unity of the left and the people's 
movement within the national political context and the 
responsibilities of the current national situation. These 
discussions will be conducted with the participation of 
political parties and movement leaders, different personalities, 
intellectuals, social and regional leaders; members of this vast 
progressive and people's sector. These opinions will be studied 
in a session at the national level. We propose to hold it as 
soon as possible so we will be allowed to establish the proposed 
Promotion Committee and thus undertake a joint Action and 
Working Plan. 
  In line with this effort to achieve the unity of the left, 
we 
hereby express our willingness to hold a constructive dialogue 
with other political and social organizations that will help 
establish a vast national civic movement for Democracy and Peace 
based on Social Justice. 
Lima, January 1994 
<H5>  Political Organizations </H5>
  Democratic Left Movement -- MDI 
  Peruvian Communist Party -- PCP 
  Socialist Revolutionary Party -- PSR 
  National Union of the Revolutionary Left -- UNIR 
