<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   CAN Party Praises Referendum, Demands Immediate Purge </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0202163994 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0202163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Guatemala Flash" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Nationalist Authentic Central (CAN) party 
leadership expressed through its general secretary, Roberto Tito 
Arana, its satisfaction with the patriotism demonstrated by the 
Guatemalan people by going to the polls to cast their vote in 
favor of the referendum. This action resulted in the approval 
of the constitutional reforms, thereby laying the foundations 
for purging Congress and the Supreme Court. The CAN leadership 
concluded by stating: "Although we are immersed in a sea of 
uncertainty and indecision, the people's will as expressed in 
the referendum compels us to demand the immediate purge of state 
institutions. As a direct consequence, elections must be held 
immediately in order not to frustrate the aspirations of the 
Guatemalan people, who for several months have been demanding 
the election of a new congress. 

</TEXT>

