<F P=100> Inter-Caribbean Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Ad Hoc Office To Sign, Seal Official Documents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0202225894 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0202225894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Given the voluntary abstentions by President Firmin 
Jean-Louis and Vice President Serge Joseph, the ad hoc office of 
the Senate, formed in compliance with the Constitution and the 
internal rules of the Senate, hastens to inform the concerned 
institutions and the entire Haitian nation that since Tuesday, 
11 January, he has been holding regular sessions at the 
Legislative Palace to take care of the business of the Republic 
during these grave, difficult times for the Haitian people. 
Consequently, any decisions and parliamentary actions resulting 
from these deliberations, duly signed by the first secretary, 
Senator Ebrane Cadet, will bear the seal of the Senate of the 
Republic for full and complete effect, states the press release 
signed by Ebrane Cadet. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

