<F P=100> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Delegation Denounces U.S. Occupation of Guantanamo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0402024594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402024594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuba has stated in Geneva that the United States 
intends to overwhelm with hunger the firm desire of our people 
to exercise their right to self-determination and independence, 
for which Cuba has been enduring a severe economic and financial 
blockade for more than 30 years. 
  Cuban Ambassador to the United Nations Jose Perez Novoa told 
the UN Human Rights Committee that the U.S. occupation of 
Guantanamo against the will of Cuba is one more example of the 
denial of that right. 
  Novoa spoke a second time today to express his position on 
point nine of the agenda, that is, free determination and its 
application to nations submitted to colonial domination or 
foreign occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

