<F P=100> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alarcon: Relations With EU `On Right Track' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0302161494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0302161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] National Assembly President Ricardo Alarcon has 
expressed his conviction that Cuba's relations with the European 
Union [EU] are on the right track; he is hoping to conclude a 
general cooperation agreement with the EU soon. 
  Alarcon is currently visiting Germany. On 2 February, in 
Bonn, he met with (Hans Klein), vice president of the German 
Parliament; deputies in charge of relations with Central America 
and the Caribbean; and representatives of the Christian 
Democratic Union, headed by Chancellor Helmut Kohl. 
  In statements to the press, Alarcon stressed: Cuba has to 
make a series of changes in its economy, but it is not seeking 
to transform the basic elements of its political design, which 
is socialism. 

</TEXT>

