<H3> <TI>   UPEC Committee Sends Message of Commitment to Castro </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0302185894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0302185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The participants in the extended plenum of the 
national committee of the Union of Cuban Journalists [UPEC], 
giving continuity to the Sixth UPEC Congress, have sent a 
message to Fidel in which they reaffirm that Cuban journalists 
will tackle today's missions with renewed energy. The letter 
states: Upon the conclusion of the agenda of our sixth congress, 
we wish to express the intense commitment this process generated 
in our journalists. 
  Two issues not fully debated in the congress because of time 
constraints were discussed in this meeting: Cuba's image abroad 
and media finances. The participants were unanimous in stressing 
the role of our media in disseminating the true image of Cuba 
and in confronting the U.S. blockade as well as the campaigns of 
the disinformation multinationals. 

</TEXT>

