<H3> <TI>   Country Elected to Chair UN Outer Space Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0402024494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402024494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuba was elected today to chair the Outer Space 
Committee [Comite del Espacio Ultraterrestre], one of the 
organizations sponsoring the UN Disarmament Conference, and 
representing the so-called Group of 21 neutral and nonaligned 
countries. 
  The decision was made in Geneva during a plenary session 
when 
the Group of 21 submitted Cuba's candidacy, which was approved 
by all members of the conference. Cuban Ambassador Jose Perez 
Novoa will head the committee which last year was chaired by the 
German representative to the Disarmament Conference. 
  The developing nations have traditionally paid special 
attention to this organization, which will now be chaired by our 
country, taking into consideration the impact the prevention of 
the arms race and the outer space program will have on the Third 
World. 

</TEXT>

