<F P=100> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ross Chairs Workers Parliament at Camaguey University </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0402031194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402031194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Relay from Los Pilajones, Camaguey Province, by Adolfo 
Silva] 
  [Text] Pedro Ross, secretary general of the Cuban Workers 
Federation and a Politburo member, has stated that during the 
workers' parliaments in the country, the workers convey their 
political perception and patriotic spirit in facing current 
problems. 
  In remarks to the press in Camaguey, Ross praised the 
positive development of these parliaments, during which the 
workers express ideas and propose solutions. Ross today chaired 
the first of the three parliaments at Camaguey University 
scheduled to discuss the economic and financial situation in the 
country and at the university. 
  Among the suggestions proposed by the workers, to be 
implemented at the university, are the better use of the budget 
without affecting the educational process, increasing the [word 
indistinct] of outstanding students, solutions to the food 
self-supply difficulties, and the control of resources. 
  The list of proposals also includes ceiling prices for 
products sold by self-employed vendors, paying for tickets to 
sports activities, collecting fees from foreign students who can 
afford to pay them, tax exemption for salaries, and increasing 
economic activity at the regional level. 

</TEXT>

